

A company needs to
  • *notice* what its customers are doing
  • *remember* what it and its customers have done over time
  • *learn* from what it has remembered (→ development/Data-mining)
  • *act* on what it has learned to make customers more profitable
  ( → development/Data-mining/Quellen/2004-Berry-Linoff_Data-Mining-Techniques, p. 3)

